rComments: I had her for the second half of GER100, and I struggled a lot. Ultimately, she went easy on me for marking and I passed with a C. She was good at explaining concepts, but has a more formal teaching style that gave the class a bit of whiplash from our previous professor's more relaxed style.

rComments: One of the best profs ever. I've still to take her exam :( but i hope its easy! Nonetheless, helps out at all times. Always a smile! FUN FUN FUN GERMAN!! Ich fuhle mich sehr gut!

She's simply the best I've ever had.  What's not to like about Ms. Schafer.  She's the only bright spot in the German department, and I wish she taught all German classes.  Always willing to help, and repeats things as often as the class wants her to.  Her patience is unbelievable!
Fantastic professor!  Very sweet lady.  Realistic and highly organized.
One of the nicest profs around.  Always willing to help and gives extensions on tests and assingments(when needed of course) for individual students.  Makes learning German worth while.
Excellent proffessor with realistic expectations.  Always willing to help and is flexible to your schedule when it is necessary.
explains things clearly. fair tests. lenient with missed assignments.
